This historic site includes buildings from the beginning of the 20th century, a chapel built in 1925 by the architect Chailleux and a garden, opened to the Parisian public in 1985. It is planted with chestnut trees, plane trees, yews, a cedar of the Himalayas and a blue Arizona cypress.
The church is very beautiful, sober and refined. The decoration for Christmas ðŸŽ… 2023 with the different nativity scenes are absolutely worth seeing. THANKS â€¦

A public garden and the coolest carousel in the neighborhood! Open outside of usual hours with a sandpit and a small slide for the little ones. The ride is a neighborhood monument for its kindness and availability, we are far from the go-go traps...

In the heart of the 16th arrondissement, there is a magnificent social work, in a wooded park, with stores that sell clothes, crockery, books, for the benefit of young people in difficulty. At the bottom of the park, there is a restaurant where you can have lunch, served by hotel apprentices who offer a delicious menu
I only know this garden during the beautiful Christmas market at the beginning of December.  It is then pleasant to wander through the pop-up shops.
